1. Keyed Collections

- These objects represent collections which use keys. The iterable collections (Map and Set) contain elements which are easily iterated in the order of insertion.

ğŸ¦Š a. Let e be the Record { [[Key]], [[Value]] } that is the value of entries[index].

ğŸ¦ŠğŸ¦Š i. Perform ? Call(callbackfn, thisArg, Â« e.[[Value]], e.[[Key]], M Â»).
ğŸ¦ŠğŸ¦Š ii. NOTE: The number of elements in entries may have increased during execution of callbackfn.
ğŸ¦ŠğŸ¦Š iii. Set numEntries to the number of elements of entries.
8. Return undefined.
